  "prompt": "What is the minimum marks needed to get mechanical branch in BITS Pilani?",
  "response": "The cutoffs for admission to various branches at BITS Pilani, including Mechanical Engineering, are determined based on the BITS Admission Test (BITSAT) score and the preferences of the candidates. The minimum marks required can vary each year depending on factors such as the number of applicants, the difficulty level of the exam, and the availability of seats.\n\nAs of recent years, the cutoff for Mechanical Engineering at BITS Pilani typically ranges between **280 to 300** out of 390 in the BITSAT exam. However, this is an approximate range and the exact cutoff can vary. It is advisable to check the official BITSAT cutoff trends or contact the institute for the most accurate and updated information.\n\nAdditionally, meeting the cutoff score does not guarantee admission, as seat allocation also depends on the order of preference filled by candidates and the competition for the branch.",
